inking about whether to include a native-image run under JDK 25. The deterministic_setup could potentially be empty. There are some risks to consider: if tests are specifically designed to cover OAuth2WebClient, then the optional OAuth2 classes will need the io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2 dependency. However, we shouldn’t add this unless the generated tests explicitly choose to use that feature. It feels important to tread carefully here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1 still resolves Vert.x Core 5.0.1 with Netty 4.2.2.Final, matching the existing 5.0.0 native-run workaround for Netty 4.2.x on Java 25; meaningful WebClient coverage can otherwise use an in-process Vert.x HTTP server without Docker or extra mandatory dependencies.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For native-image runtime verification on JDK 25, ensure the generated/updated test build applies the same nativeTest runtime system properties for 5.0.1 as 5.0.0: -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true. Tests should create a local Vert.x HttpServer and WebClient for GET/POST/forms/multipart/cache/session coverage; no external service is required.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"OAuth2WebClient is present in the artifact but depends on optional io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2; avoid covering OAuth2-specific APIs unless intentionally adding that optional dependency.\",\n    \"Local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative for whether the Netty/JDK 25 system properties are still sufficient.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_060ba21374406768016a402bed507c8193b681ec0f2841006e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1570, "output": 799, "cacheRead": 22528, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24897, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cach